OREON Gearbox Maintenance Manual

Gearbox wear indicators include oil temperature increase, vibration, gear mesh noise, metallic
particles in oil, elevated bearing temperatures, backlash growth, and visible pitting on gear teeth.

Lubrication failure is commonly caused by blocked oil filters, low oil level, wrong viscosity,
water contamination, failed oil pump, or clogged breathers. Corrective actions: drain and inspect oil,
replace filters, flush casing, inspect bearings and gear teeth by borescope, and restore lubrication
flow before restart.
